(827, 0, 'Oana Silviana Craciun', 'oana.silvia2008@gmail.com', 'Other', NULL, 'All', 'Yes', 'No', NULL, NULL, '0726023193', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0612202021_Oana Silviana Craciun/0612202021_cv.doc', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'active', NULL, 'Dear Sir/ Madam, \n\nI am writing to express my enthusiasm and interest in opportunities within your organisation and to outline the ways in which I believe my skills, qualifications and experience in the communications field would make me a very valuable addition to your team.\n\nPassionate about all aspects of the communication and tourism industry, I have over 10 years’ wide-ranging production, broadcasting, journalism, and content development experience gained in leading television and publishing companies in my native Romania, and I am an accomplished PR professional.\n\nTourism is my 3rd professional specialty, accomplished while working in the field and through professional courses.\n\nMy personal website, www.fairytaletraveller.com, is a continuation of a year-long travel series I presented on National Tourism Television in Romania. Working closely with travel agencies from all over the world and managing all aspects of production for the show, I researched and promoted memorable locations both within Romania and abroad. \n\nI also worked for a recruiting agency in the UK as a recruitment consultant and PR representative for the hospitality industry, building the company&#39;s brand awareness abroad and providing the best recruiting services both internal and external. \n\nAs a volunteer and PR Professional for almost 5 years for my local branch of international NGO United Hands, which supports orphaned children and needy families, I delivered comprehensive PR services including social media management and planned and executed a number of successful fundraising projects and events.\n\nI am looking to build my career while making full use of my skills and experience to add value. I would love to work within an organisation where I can develop my skills, take on interesting, challenging projects, and work with people from whom I can really learn, sharing the same values inside a company.\n\nMy enclosed portfolio provides an overview of my work to date and as you will see from my CV, I hold a Master’s degree in Communication and Public Relations from the National School of Political and Administrative Studies in Bucharest as well as a Bachelor’s degree in Mass Communication and Journalism. I have completed a number of media-related professional development courses, and I am a fluent and confident communicator in spoken and written English. \n\nYour organisation’s goals for the future are exciting, and I would greatly welcome the opportunity to contribute to the ongoing success of your work. \n\nI am interested in opened positions for the following fields: Marketing, Public Relations, Communication, Media, Advertising, Tourism. \n\nThank you for considering my application, and I hope we can arrange an interview to discuss it in greater depth. Please do not hesitate to call me or write me, in order to do so.\n\n\n\nSincerely,\nOana Silviana Crăciun\nenc.: CV and Portfolio', '2020-12-06 16:36:21', '2020-12-06 16:36:21'),
